# Kubernetes Namespaces

Namespaces are used to **group Kubernetes resources**.

Example grouping

```
frontend-app-pods → frontend namespace
backend-app-pods → backend namespace
database-pods → database namespace
```

We can create **multiple namespaces in a Kubernetes cluster**.

Example

```
ashokit-a1-ns
ashokit-a2-ns
```

Each namespace is **isolated from other namespaces**.

Important Note

When we delete a namespace, **all resources inside that namespace are deleted automatically**.

---

# Display Namespaces

```bash
kubectl get ns
```

---

# Get Pods from Specific Namespace

Example: pods from kube-system namespace

```bash
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
```

If namespace is not specified, Kubernetes uses the **default namespace**.

---

# Create Namespace

Namespaces can be created in **two ways**.

---

## Approach 1: Using Command

```bash
kubectl create ns ashokit-ns
```

---

## Approach 2: Using Manifest YAML

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: ashokit-ns-2
```

Apply YAML

```bash
kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml
```

---

# Delete Namespace

```bash
kubectl delete ns <namespace-name>
```

Example

```bash
kubectl delete ns ashokit-ns
```

---

# Example: Namespace + Pod + Service in One YAML

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: ashokit-ns

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: javawebapppod
  namespace: ashokit-ns
  labels:
    app: javawebapp

spec:
  containers:
  - name: javawebappcontainer
    image: ashokit/javawebapp
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8080

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: javawebappsvc
  namespace: ashokit-ns

spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: javawebapp

  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 8080
```

Apply YAML

```bash
kubectl apply -f manifest.yaml
```

---

# Verify Namespace Resources

Check namespaces

```bash
kubectl get ns
```

Check pods inside namespace

```bash
kubectl get pods -n ashokit-ns
```

Check services inside namespace

```bash
kubectl get service -n ashokit-ns
```

Check all resources inside namespace

```bash
kubectl get all -n ashokit-ns
```

---

# Delete Namespace

Deleting the namespace removes **all resources inside it**.

```bash
kubectl delete ns ashokit-ns
```

